features: "Swift and Efficient Power-Up: Experience rapid charging with the Anker 323 Charger, fortified with a robust 33W USB-C Power Delivery port. This powerhouse charges your devices up to 3 times faster than standard chargers, making it an ideal match for iPhones, iPads, Galaxy, Pixel, and more.

Simultaneous Dual-Port Charging: Our innovative 2-in-1 design incorporates both a USB-C and a USB-A port, allowing you to power up two devices concurrently, maximizing your time and boosting charging productivity.

Ultra-Compact and Travel-Ready: With its sleek, compact design and foldable plug, this charger is your ultimate travel partner. Effortlessly slip it into your bag, backpack, or pocket and stay powered up wherever you go.

Superior Safety Mechanisms: Outfitted with the cutting-edge ActiveShield Safety System, this charger offers continuous temperature monitoring and output control, delivering unparalleled protection for your devices against potential overheating and overcharging.

Complete Package: Your purchase comes with the Anker 323 Charger (33W), a comprehensive welcome guide, our stress-free 18-month warranty, and the support of our dedicated and approachable customer service team."

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 27, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Excellent charger for my security cameras
reviews.reviewText: I use the small charger to plug in my Arlo security cameras. This keeps the batteries always charged and the cameras are always on 24/7. Normal plug in adapters did not always transfer the right amount of power to keep the cameras batteries charged 100%. With the 33W, Anker 323 Charger the cameras are always reading full battery without over heating or warping. Highly recommend these chargers but always refer to the owners manual of the device you are going to use this charger with. Price was very budget friendly and the weight of the charge is no issue. Adapter stays plugged into the outlet and does not fall off or pull out on its own.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 11, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Anker products have achieved a solid rep despite their origin
reviews.reviewText: This is the second set of Anker plugs I have bought . Solid and functional they are a reasonably priced alternative to charge USB-A and /or USB-C. Love how small they are and while there are plugs that can deliver more power these 333 watt are more than adequate . A good buy

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 6, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Anker strikes again
reviews.reviewText: Needed another plug to replace a much older Anker one that I used very often - as expected, Anker did not let me down. Works well and charges fast. Seems to be very well made as compared against some companies plugs. Good job Anker.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 18, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Nice compact high wattage charge
reviews.reviewText: Super fast phone charge! Works great.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 5, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Works well and very portable
reviews.reviewText: This is my idea of perfect for traveling. The USB-C port provides enough power to keep my small laptop going, and can even top off the battery while in the laptop is in use. The USB-A port can charge other items (headphones, watches, phones) at the same time. Small and light.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 12, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Awesome travel charger, but intermittent
reviews.reviewText: This is an awesome 2 port travel charger. It's compact with a foldable plug that doesn't take up much space. And both ports are powerful enough for fast charging even when both ports are being used simultaneously. But, the USB-A port on mine has started working only intermittently. Not sure if it's a defect but at least the USB-C port works flawlessly as it's the one that I use the most.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 30, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Another winner from Anker
reviews.reviewText: This just works! It does what it says it will do. I realized as I've been upgrading phones that I haven't been updating travel chargers or cords. I bought this on a prime day sale and really feel like it's a good value. While it isn't a super fast charging speed for my Samsung S29 FE, it is fast charging and works well, especially for the price.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 18, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Compact but powerful
reviews.reviewText: Two fast charge output ports and folding prongs make this a winner, just as I expected from my go-to brand for chargers, speakers and earbuds.
Would recommend this brand any time without hesitation. The charger is small but works great,

reviews.reviewTitle: Quick Charging For Google Pixel 8 Pro
reviews.reviewText: Quick Charging for my Google Pixel 8 Pro. Great price for this quality made product.
I use it to power my Creative Pebble Pro and they are wonderful.The fact that they have a full sized USB A port along with a USB C is super useful!

reviews.reviewTitle: Works Good with iPhone 15 Pro Max
reviews.reviewText: It charges my iPhone 15 pro max quite fast. It saves some space in your backpack as you have a usb port.

Larger than others, and pricier. But it doesn't BUZZ, can charge two devices simultaneously at decent rates for both, and charges my Pixel 8pro at very close to the phone's max of 30W PD. Great for travel.
